article.headline: Toledo 68, Akron 65
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Florentino Valencia scored 17 points and made a layup that put Toledo ahead to stay in the closing minutes Saturday night, setting up a 68-65 victory over Akron. Toledo (13-10, 9-2 Mid-American) overcame an early 12-point deficit, setting up a back-and-forth finish that featured five lead changes in the last 5 minutes. Ridley Johnson and Kashif Payne added 16 points apiece for the Rockets. Nick Dials scored 17 points for Akron (18-5, 9-2), which missed its last six shots and had a turnover. Dru Joyce missed a 3-pointer to tie with 1 second left. Dials made all of his five shots from behind the arc, two of them during a 19-7 run that opened the game. Payne led a 15-7 spurt that cut it to 37-34 at halftime, making a 3-pointer, a jumper, a layup and a pair of free throws. Payne's free throw tied it at 37 early in the second half. Akron pulled ahead by as many as seven points, but Justin Ingram's 3-pointer -- his only basket in 10 shots -- tied it at 61 with 5:44 to play and set up the close finish. Valencia's layup put Toledo ahead 66-65 with 3 minutes left.
